00:02:30.960 --> 00:02:32.140 align:middle line:90%
in our reality.

00:02:32.140 --> 00:02:34.940 align:middle line:84%
And this is something
that we-- it's actually

00:02:34.940 --> 00:02:37.560 align:middle line:84%
a good point of
departure to answer

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:39.970 align:middle line:84%
the questions, the many
questions that people come up

00:02:39.970 --> 00:02:42.950 align:middle line:84%
with, the 13 or
whatever frequently

00:02:42.950 --> 00:02:46.320 align:middle line:84%
asked questions is
start from the premise

00:02:46.320 --> 00:02:48.490 align:middle line:90%
that everything changes.

00:02:48.490 --> 00:02:50.720 align:middle line:84%
And we have to ask
ourselves, whatever

00:02:50.720 --> 00:02:53.287 align:middle line:84%
question it is that
people throw at you--

00:02:53.287 --> 00:02:55.120 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to end
off this whole series

00:02:55.120 --> 00:02:58.310 align:middle line:84%
with those questions again and
throw other questions that we

00:02:58.310 --> 00:03:01.800 align:middle line:84%
come up with here in the
studio and see how easily we

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:03.660 align:middle line:90%
can solve any problem.

00:03:03.660 --> 00:03:08.540 align:middle line:84%
There is no problem
that cannot be solved,

00:03:08.540 --> 00:03:11.060 align:middle line:84%
because it's a
self-correcting system.

00:03:11.060 --> 00:03:13.460 align:middle line:84%
It always corrects itself
for the best outcome

00:03:13.460 --> 00:03:14.790 align:middle line:90%
of the community.

00:03:14.790 --> 00:03:16.870 align:middle line:84%
And that's why we can
solve all the problems.

00:03:16.870 --> 00:03:17.840 align:middle line:90%
It's not complicated.

00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:19.120 align:middle line:90%
It's very simple.

00:03:19.120 --> 00:03:22.990 align:middle line:84%
So the way we can approach these
questions when they come up

00:03:22.990 --> 00:03:27.080 align:middle line:84%
is to rather ask a
question in return.

00:03:27.080 --> 00:03:30.260 align:middle line:84%
How will this work in
a world without money?

00:03:30.260 --> 00:03:35.020 align:middle line:84%
So when people say, well, what's
going to happen to education?

00:03:35.020 --> 00:03:38.300 align:middle line:84%
The question is, well, will
we have schools the way

00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:39.960 align:middle line:90%
we have schools today?

00:03:39.960 --> 00:03:43.250 align:middle line:84%
Or if people say, what's going
to happen to cars in a world

00:03:43.250 --> 00:03:44.050 align:middle line:90%
without money?

00:03:44.050 --> 00:03:45.850 align:middle line:84%
And the question
is, well, well we

00:03:45.850 --> 00:03:47.950 align:middle line:90%
drive the cars we drive today?

00:03:47.950 --> 00:03:51.690 align:middle line:84%
Will we still use petrol
the way we use petrol today?

00:03:51.690 --> 00:03:52.530 align:middle line:90%
And so it goes.

00:03:52.530 --> 00:03:55.310 align:middle line:84%
Will we need roads the
way we have roads today?

00:03:55.310 --> 00:03:57.220 align:middle line:84%
And the answer to do
that is no, we're not,

00:03:57.220 --> 00:03:59.110 align:middle line:90%
because that's going to change.

00:03:59.110 --> 00:04:02.580 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to use the cars
in the way we use cars today.

00:04:02.580 --> 00:04:05.150 align:middle line:84%
Transportation will
change completely.

00:04:05.150 --> 00:04:09.310 align:middle line:84%
Will we have airplanes using the
same technology we use today?

00:04:09.310 --> 00:04:12.520 align:middle line:84%
The answer to that is, most
likely not, most probably not,

00:04:12.520 --> 00:04:16.200 align:middle line:84%
most definitely not, because
if we set our scientists free,

00:04:16.200 --> 00:04:20.000 align:middle line:84%
that technology is going to be
replaced very, very quickly.

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:22.350 align:middle line:84%
And that applies to every
aspect of our lives.

00:04:22.350 --> 00:04:25.710 align:middle line:84%
And the moment you remove
money, those questions

00:04:25.710 --> 00:04:27.190 align:middle line:90%
can be solved very quickly.

00:04:27.190 --> 00:04:31.200 align:middle line:84%
Then we get to this
Labor Of Love, the LOL.

00:04:31.200 --> 00:04:33.310 align:middle line:84%
Remember, in a
world without money,

00:04:33.310 --> 00:04:36.190 align:middle line:84%
there are no jobs,
because you're now

00:04:36.190 --> 00:04:38.630 align:middle line:90%
fulfilling your life purpose.

00:04:38.630 --> 00:04:41.740 align:middle line:84%
You're giving expression
to your creative needs

00:04:41.740 --> 00:04:45.120 align:middle line:90%
and what drives you from within.

00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:51.900 align:middle line:84%
So we call it a labor of love
and not a job or your life work

00:04:51.900 --> 00:04:53.580 align:middle line:90%
that you choose to do.

00:04:53.580 --> 00:04:55.350 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it is that
you choose to do,

00:04:55.350 --> 00:04:57.750 align:middle line:84%
whether you're a shoemaker
or a rocket scientist

00:04:57.750 --> 00:05:00.650 align:middle line:84%
or a sculptor or a
chemical engineer

00:05:00.650 --> 00:05:03.020 align:middle line:84%
or a baker, whatever
it is-- or you

00:05:03.020 --> 00:05:05.480 align:middle line:84%
breed horses for your
community, whatever

00:05:05.480 --> 00:05:07.990 align:middle line:84%
it is that you love
to do will ultimately

00:05:07.990 --> 00:05:11.120 align:middle line:84%
become part of your community
and serve your community

00:05:11.120 --> 00:05:12.190 align:middle line:90%
in some way.

00:05:12.190 --> 00:05:15.770 align:middle line:84%
So sooner or later, whatever
it is you choose to do

00:05:15.770 --> 00:05:18.850 align:middle line:84%
will most likely become
a community project.

00:05:18.850 --> 00:05:21.650 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of the most
amazing things to realize,

00:05:21.650 --> 00:05:25.320 align:middle line:84%
how what you do actually
affects and impacts and benefits

00:05:25.320 --> 00:05:27.340 align:middle line:90%
everyone in your community.

00:05:27.340 --> 00:05:29.780 align:middle line:84%
And this is why it's a
one-to-many exchange.

00:05:29.780 --> 00:05:32.700 align:middle line:84%
It's not a bartering
or trading system.

00:05:32.700 --> 00:05:37.080 align:middle line:84%
It is a one-to-many exchange
so everybody benefits

00:05:37.080 --> 00:05:39.990 align:middle line:84%
from everything
that everybody does.

00:05:39.990 --> 00:05:41.440 align:middle line:84%
Then the council
of elders, we've

00:05:41.440 --> 00:05:43.920 align:middle line:84%
discussed how important
it is to implement

00:05:43.920 --> 00:05:44.840 align:middle line:90%
the council of elders.

00:05:44.840 --> 00:05:50.500 align:middle line:84%
So this is the guiding body,
the body of wise people

00:05:50.500 --> 00:05:53.130 align:middle line:84%
that are appointed
from the community that

00:05:53.130 --> 00:05:59.250 align:middle line:84%
guide and govern and advise
the community what's best.

00:05:59.250 --> 00:06:01.664 align:middle line:84%
So if I come up
with an idea, wow,

00:06:01.664 --> 00:06:03.830 align:middle line:84%
I want to build a foofy
slide from the mountain down

00:06:03.830 --> 00:06:07.560 align:middle line:84%
to my garden and I want
everybody to help me build it,

00:06:07.560 --> 00:06:10.160 align:middle line:84%
the council of elders will
probably say, listen, Michael,

00:06:10.160 --> 00:06:14.430 align:middle line:84%
you're a nice guy, but if we're
going to build a foofy slide,

00:06:14.430 --> 00:06:16.290 align:middle line:84%
let's not build
it to your garden.

00:06:16.290 --> 00:06:17.970 align:middle line:84%
Let's build a foofy
slide from the top

00:06:17.970 --> 00:06:20.430 align:middle line:84%
of the mountain to
the park so everybody

00:06:20.430 --> 00:06:23.330 align:middle line:84%
can use the foofy
slide and not just you,

00:06:23.330 --> 00:06:25.930 align:middle line:84%
because these kind of
things will happen.

00:06:25.930 --> 00:06:28.000 align:middle line:84%
So I'm using a silly
example, but to show you

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.235 align:middle line:84%
how easily these things can be
solved, because, yes, people

00:06:32.235 --> 00:06:34.430 align:middle line:84%
will still want to do
things for their own benefit

00:06:34.430 --> 00:06:37.500 align:middle line:84%
while we're getting
over this sharing thing

00:06:37.500 --> 00:06:41.180 align:middle line:84%
and we don't really do
things for ourselves anymore.

00:06:41.180 --> 00:06:42.982 align:middle line:84%
Of course, your home
will be your home.

00:06:42.982 --> 00:06:44.440 align:middle line:84%
Your furniture will
be your choice.

00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:46.523 align:middle line:84%
The kind of clothes you
wear will be your clothes.

00:06:46.523 --> 00:06:48.790 align:middle line:90%
And everything is made for you.

00:06:48.790 --> 00:06:51.561 align:middle line:84%
It's custom made for you
because that's how it works.

00:06:51.561 --> 00:06:54.060 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to go into a
shop and get it off the shelf,

00:06:54.060 --> 00:06:55.601 align:middle line:84%
because we're not
going to have shops

00:06:55.601 --> 00:06:59.450 align:middle line:84%
where things sit getting ready
waiting for people to buy them.

00:06:59.450 --> 00:07:02.620 align:middle line:84%
That no longer exists, so that
changes when you take money out

00:07:02.620 --> 00:07:03.420 align:middle line:90%
of the system.

00:07:03.420 --> 00:07:06.305 align:middle line:84%
The way we shop, the
way we get things, well,

00:07:06.305 --> 00:07:08.820 align:middle line:84%
we're not going to be shopping,
but how we get and attain

00:07:08.820 --> 00:07:10.680 align:middle line:90%
things changes completely.

00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:13.350 align:middle line:84%
That's where the council of
elders comes in and guides

00:07:13.350 --> 00:07:17.000 align:middle line:84%
and make sure that people
don't abuse the system

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:18.530 align:middle line:90%
for their own personal benefit.

00:07:18.530 --> 00:07:20.170 align:middle line:84%
And then the minority
rule principle

00:07:20.170 --> 00:07:25.520 align:middle line:84%
is important to consider, where
all the minorities, no matter

00:07:25.520 --> 00:07:28.630 align:middle line:84%
how small the group
of individuals

00:07:28.630 --> 00:07:31.890 align:middle line:84%
may be, because
they're performing

00:07:31.890 --> 00:07:35.230 align:middle line:84%
an important task
or important support

00:07:35.230 --> 00:07:39.040 align:middle line:84%
or anything for the community,
they need to be supported.

00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:42.690 align:middle line:84%
They need to be given all the
tools, the scientific research.

00:07:42.690 --> 00:07:44.690 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it is
you're doing, you'll

00:07:44.690 --> 00:07:48.080 align:middle line:84%
be given-- if you're doing this
and it benefits the community.

00:07:48.080 --> 00:07:50.217 align:middle line:84%
Then the one thing
we didn't touch upon

00:07:50.217 --> 00:07:52.300 align:middle line:84%
is the lone ranger, because
not everybody is going

00:07:52.300 --> 00:07:53.622 align:middle line:90%
to want to live in a community.

00:07:53.622 --> 00:07:55.580 align:middle line:84%
What if you want to go
and live out on your own

00:07:55.580 --> 00:07:58.140 align:middle line:84%
somewhere on a farm
in the mountains?

00:07:58.140 --> 00:07:59.990 align:middle line:84%
Then that's what
you're going to do.

00:07:59.990 --> 00:08:03.630 align:middle line:84%
But again, things are now
going to change, because today

00:08:03.630 --> 00:08:09.140 align:middle line:84%
when people are out on farms,
they often farm things, right?

00:08:09.140 --> 00:08:12.450 align:middle line:84%
They either farm
cattle or huge tracts

00:08:12.450 --> 00:08:15.026 align:middle line:90%
of land of maize or whatever.

00:08:15.026 --> 00:08:16.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's no longer
going to happen,

00:08:16.650 --> 00:08:18.930 align:middle line:84%
because you're not going
to be able to sell that.

00:08:18.930 --> 00:08:19.730 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:08:19.730 --> 00:08:21.030 align:middle line:90%
You're going to have 400 cows.

00:08:21.030 --> 00:08:23.151 align:middle line:84%
It's a lot of work to
look after 400 cows.

00:08:23.151 --> 00:08:25.150 align:middle line:84%
And you're not going to
have people helping you,

00:08:25.150 --> 00:08:27.441 align:middle line:84%
because you're not going to
be paying them to help you.

00:08:27.441 --> 00:08:29.070 align:middle line:90%
So that whole thing changes.

00:08:29.070 --> 00:08:33.340 align:middle line:84%
So you're going to do
and occupy as much land

00:08:33.340 --> 00:08:37.440 align:middle line:84%
as you need to serve your
community, your community that

00:08:37.440 --> 00:08:38.900 align:middle line:90%
belongs to your family.

00:08:38.900 --> 00:08:41.880 align:middle line:84%
So if you have a family of
five or six or 10 people,

00:08:41.880 --> 00:08:44.220 align:middle line:84%
then you're probably going
to only use up so much space

00:08:44.220 --> 00:08:48.570 align:middle line:84%
that you need to serve your
community on your little piece

00:08:48.570 --> 00:08:51.920 align:middle line:90%
of land wherever that may be.

00:08:51.920 --> 00:08:55.127 align:middle line:84%
So you're not going to
grow 20 acres of maize,

00:08:55.127 --> 00:08:57.460 align:middle line:84%
because you're not going to
need that and it's too much.

00:08:57.460 --> 00:08:59.470 align:middle line:84%
What are you going to
do with the rest of it?

00:08:59.470 --> 00:09:00.680 align:middle line:90%
You can't eat all of it.

00:09:00.680 --> 00:09:02.350 align:middle line:90%
You can't sell it to anybody.

00:09:02.350 --> 00:09:04.400 align:middle line:90%
See how that changes?

00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:08.900 align:middle line:84%
So the Lone Ranger aspect
is a very exciting part

00:09:08.900 --> 00:09:11.560 align:middle line:84%
of this evolution
and how this works.

00:09:11.560 --> 00:09:13.830 align:middle line:84%
So you can go and
live out on your own,

00:09:13.830 --> 00:09:16.770 align:middle line:84%
but sooner or later, you're
going to probably interact

00:09:16.770 --> 00:09:18.199 align:middle line:90%
with the closest community.

00:09:18.199 --> 00:09:19.990 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to go
in there once a week

00:09:19.990 --> 00:09:22.610 align:middle line:84%
and perform some task
for that community

00:09:22.610 --> 00:09:26.320 align:middle line:84%
so you can benefit from whatever
that community is doing.

00:09:26.320 --> 00:09:28.490 align:middle line:84%
And then you can carry on
living as a lone ranger,

00:09:28.490 --> 00:09:30.130 align:middle line:90%
because you don't like company.

00:09:30.130 --> 00:09:31.500 align:middle line:90%
You want to be on your own.

00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:35.170 align:middle line:84%
And then you have the benefits
and the best of both worlds.

00:09:35.170 --> 00:09:36.670 align:middle line:84%
And nobody's going
to mess with you,

00:09:36.670 --> 00:09:38.686 align:middle line:84%
because you're not taking
up unnecessary space.

00:09:38.686 --> 00:09:40.560 align:middle line:84%
You're not claiming all
this land and saying,

00:09:40.560 --> 00:09:42.450 align:middle line:84%
this is my land,
get off my land,

00:09:42.450 --> 00:09:45.890 align:middle line:84%
because you don't need to
have 400 cows so you've

00:09:45.890 --> 00:09:47.930 align:middle line:90%
got security for the future.

00:09:47.930 --> 00:09:49.622 align:middle line:84%
You don't need to
grow all this food,

00:09:49.622 --> 00:09:51.330 align:middle line:84%
because you've got
all the food you need,

00:09:51.330 --> 00:09:54.080 align:middle line:84%
because you're still part
of the nearest community.

00:09:54.080 --> 00:09:55.670 align:middle line:90%
You can choose not to do that.

00:09:55.670 --> 00:09:58.420 align:middle line:84%
But that's just going to make
it more difficult for yourself.

00:09:58.420 --> 00:10:01.410 align:middle line:84%
So it's a lot better just to
participate in the closest

00:10:01.410 --> 00:10:04.890 align:middle line:84%
community activity and then
have the benefits of all

00:10:04.890 --> 00:10:07.332 align:middle line:90%
that community produces.

00:10:07.332 --> 00:10:09.290 align:middle line:84%
So the Lone Ranger thing
I find quite exciting.

00:10:09.290 --> 00:10:11.490 align:middle line:84%
And it's a great
example to show how

00:10:11.490 --> 00:10:15.240 align:middle line:84%
things change for the
benefit of those that choose

00:10:15.240 --> 00:10:17.570 align:middle line:90%
to live out on their own.

00:10:17.570 --> 00:10:22.510 align:middle line:84%
And again, remember that land
ownership flies out the window.

00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:24.400 align:middle line:90%
There is no land ownership.

00:10:24.400 --> 00:10:28.920 align:middle line:84%
People use land and
space based on what

00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:30.860 align:middle line:84%
it is they're doing
for the community.

00:10:30.860 --> 00:10:34.290 align:middle line:84%
So if you're a shoemaker, you
don't need 100 acres of land,

00:10:34.290 --> 00:10:35.090 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:10:35.090 --> 00:10:37.970 align:middle line:84%
But if you're participating in
growing food for the community,

00:10:37.970 --> 00:10:38.770 align:middle line:90%
that changes.

00:10:38.770 --> 00:10:41.450 align:middle line:84%
Then you will use
as much land as it

00:10:41.450 --> 00:10:43.280 align:middle line:84%
takes to grow the food
for the community.

00:10:43.280 --> 00:10:45.834 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to use
less or more, because we

00:10:45.834 --> 00:10:48.250 align:middle line:84%
know how much food we're going
to grow, so that's how much

00:10:48.250 --> 00:10:49.330 align:middle line:90%
land we use.

00:10:49.330 --> 00:10:52.140 align:middle line:84%
So this whole thing of
ownership of land and I've

00:10:52.140 --> 00:10:56.324 align:middle line:84%
got all this land belongs to me,
me, me, that no longer exists.

00:10:56.324 --> 00:10:58.490 align:middle line:84%
And if you want to move
from this town to that town,

00:10:58.490 --> 00:11:01.010 align:middle line:84%
then that's what
you do, because you

00:11:01.010 --> 00:11:02.830 align:middle line:84%
choose to move to
another community

00:11:02.830 --> 00:11:05.760 align:middle line:84%
because you've had enough living
in the mountains and the snow.

00:11:05.760 --> 00:11:09.980 align:middle line:84%
You want to go and live near the
beach where the coconuts grow.

00:11:09.980 --> 00:11:11.040 align:middle line:90%
That's your choice.

00:11:11.040 --> 00:11:13.860 align:middle line:84%
And when you arrive there,
they welcome you with open arms

00:11:13.860 --> 00:11:16.800 align:middle line:84%
and you plug into this community
and you get a beautiful place

00:11:16.800 --> 00:11:17.600 align:middle line:90%
to live.

00:11:17.600 --> 00:11:19.600 align:middle line:84%
Or if there is no house
for you to live in,

00:11:19.600 --> 00:11:23.770 align:middle line:84%
then you have one
built for yourself,

00:11:23.770 --> 00:11:27.080 align:middle line:84%
because that's what the
builders and the architects do.

00:11:27.080 --> 00:11:29.430 align:middle line:84%
They design your home
based on what you like

00:11:29.430 --> 00:11:30.334 align:middle line:90%
and what you want.

00:11:30.334 --> 00:11:31.750 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, there
are restrictions.

00:11:31.750 --> 00:11:34.280 align:middle line:84%
They're not going to
build a 20-room mansion up

00:11:34.280 --> 00:11:38.180 align:middle line:84%
on the mountain, because you
have to clean your house.

00:11:38.180 --> 00:11:40.940 align:middle line:84%
So again, all of
that kicks in, right?

00:11:40.940 --> 00:11:43.260 align:middle line:84%
So why do you want
a 20-room mansion?

00:11:43.260 --> 00:11:46.450 align:middle line:84%
Today, people have 20-room
mansions because it's value,

00:11:46.450 --> 00:11:47.580 align:middle line:90%
perceived value.

00:11:47.580 --> 00:11:50.070 align:middle line:84%
It's worth a lot more
than a little small room.

00:11:50.070 --> 00:11:53.090 align:middle line:84%
Well, you see how quickly
people's perception

00:11:53.090 --> 00:11:56.610 align:middle line:84%
change when they no longer
see it as something of value

00:11:56.610 --> 00:11:58.800 align:middle line:84%
that they could sell
to make some money

00:11:58.800 --> 00:12:00.520 align:middle line:90%
to have a retirement.

00:12:00.520 --> 00:12:02.000 align:middle line:90%
Everything changes.

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:03.790 align:middle line:84%
I want to live in a
mud hut on the beach.

00:12:03.790 --> 00:12:05.900 align:middle line:90%
That's my personal wish.

00:12:05.900 --> 00:12:09.040 align:middle line:84%
I want to live in the land
of the low-hanging fruits

00:12:09.040 --> 00:12:14.800 align:middle line:84%
in a mud hut near the
beach, where I can just

00:12:14.800 --> 00:12:16.810 align:middle line:90%
live in warm climates.

00:12:16.810 --> 00:12:18.960 align:middle line:84%
I don't like the
cold climate at all.

00:12:18.960 --> 00:12:21.540 align:middle line:84%
And that's another thing
that people ask you.

00:12:21.540 --> 00:12:23.540 align:middle line:84%
People say-- often they
use it as an argument,

00:12:23.540 --> 00:12:25.660 align:middle line:84%
say, well, everybody's going
to want to live on the beach.

00:12:25.660 --> 00:12:26.580 align:middle line:90%
Really?

00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:27.530 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:12:27.530 --> 00:12:29.029 align:middle line:84%
You might want to
live on the beach.

00:12:29.029 --> 00:12:30.446 align:middle line:84%
But I know that
him, her, and her,

00:12:30.446 --> 00:12:31.904 align:middle line:84%
they want to live
on the mountains,

00:12:31.904 --> 00:12:33.240 align:middle line:90%
because they like snowboarding.

00:12:33.240 --> 00:12:35.230 align:middle line:84%
They want to live
where the snow is.

00:12:35.230 --> 00:12:37.270 align:middle line:84%
They don't want to live
anywhere near the beach.

00:12:37.270 --> 00:12:38.603 align:middle line:90%
And some people like the rivers.

00:12:38.603 --> 00:12:41.010 align:middle line:90%
Some people like the desert.

00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:44.100 align:middle line:84%
There are as many preferences
as there are people.

00:12:44.100 --> 00:12:45.980 align:middle line:84%
So this whole notion
that everybody

00:12:45.980 --> 00:12:49.600 align:middle line:84%
wants to live on a beach is
another capitalistic poisoning

00:12:49.600 --> 00:12:53.120 align:middle line:84%
of our minds how we've
been completely baffled

00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:57.430 align:middle line:84%
by the system that we've
grown into or born into.

00:12:57.430 --> 00:12:59.660 align:middle line:84%
Finally on this
important considerations

00:12:59.660 --> 00:13:05.510 align:middle line:84%
list is this whole process is
a process of no confrontation.

00:13:05.510 --> 00:13:07.000 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to
confront anybody.

00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.480 align:middle line:90%
We don't have to oppose anybody.

00:13:08.480 --> 00:13:13.950 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to take up arms
against anybody or get violent.

00:13:13.950 --> 00:13:18.290 align:middle line:84%
All we do is we just create
this new alternative.

00:13:18.290 --> 00:13:20.940 align:middle line:84%
And the moment we create
this new alternative,

00:13:20.940 --> 00:13:26.030 align:middle line:84%
we've started a chain reaction
that can no longer be stopped.

00:13:26.030 --> 00:13:28.550 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to confront or
fight or argue with anybody

00:13:28.550 --> 00:13:32.260 align:middle line:84%
or convince any
government of anything.

00:13:32.260 --> 00:13:35.320 align:middle line:84%
Just create a new path
for ourselves, a new path

00:13:35.320 --> 00:13:37.690 align:middle line:90%
away from the global control.

00:13:37.690 --> 00:13:41.880 align:middle line:84%
And that brings us to one of
the foundations of our poisoned

00:13:41.880 --> 00:13:44.010 align:middle line:90%
society, and that is education.

00:13:44.010 --> 00:13:46.100 align:middle line:84%
And this really is one
of my favorite subjects,

00:13:46.100 --> 00:13:49.880 align:middle line:84%
because this is where you really
start seeing how quickly we can

00:13:49.880 --> 00:13:53.710 align:middle line:84%
convert our society and
our children into really

00:13:53.710 --> 00:13:57.320 align:middle line:84%
well-balanced individuals,
well integrated into

00:13:57.320 --> 00:13:59.850 align:middle line:84%
their communities,
that truly start

00:13:59.850 --> 00:14:04.010 align:middle line:84%
adding to the well-being
of their community

00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:06.250 align:middle line:90%
from the earliest of ages.

00:14:06.250 --> 00:14:09.150 align:middle line:84%
So all the community
projects that we

00:14:09.150 --> 00:14:11.940 align:middle line:84%
have that you're going
to participate in,

00:14:11.940 --> 00:14:14.670 align:middle line:84%
they're actually going to
become the new education system.

00:14:14.670 --> 00:14:18.270 align:middle line:84%
You can imagine after a while--
and not only for the adults,

00:14:18.270 --> 00:14:20.380 align:middle line:90%
for the children as well.

00:14:20.380 --> 00:14:23.930 align:middle line:84%
So what we propose with
the Ubuntu philosophy

00:14:23.930 --> 00:14:26.230 align:middle line:84%
is that there are
really no schools.

00:14:26.230 --> 00:14:30.550 align:middle line:84%
It's complete unschooling
and unlearning and learning

00:14:30.550 --> 00:14:33.740 align:middle line:84%
hands-on, experiential
learning skills for life

00:14:33.740 --> 00:14:35.170 align:middle line:90%
from the earliest of age.

00:14:35.170 --> 00:14:38.090 align:middle line:84%
Of course, there are going
to be gatherings of children,

00:14:38.090 --> 00:14:41.070 align:middle line:84%
and teachers who are really--
who love teaching, who

00:14:41.070 --> 00:14:43.840 align:middle line:84%
know the art of
teaching, that understand

00:14:43.840 --> 00:14:47.300 align:middle line:84%
that play and interaction
with children is critical.

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:51.460 align:middle line:84%
As Plato said, without the
element of play and games,

00:14:51.460 --> 00:14:53.910 align:middle line:84%
children really
don't learn much.

00:14:53.910 --> 00:14:56.120 align:middle line:90%
So we need to implement this.

00:14:56.120 --> 00:14:59.880 align:middle line:84%
And there are master teachers
that really understand

00:14:59.880 --> 00:15:02.610 align:middle line:84%
how to bring this forth
and how to bring out

00:15:02.610 --> 00:15:05.170 align:middle line:84%
the best in the
children in this kind

00:15:05.170 --> 00:15:09.240 align:middle line:84%
of interactive, participatory
way of teaching and learning

00:15:09.240 --> 00:15:10.900 align:middle line:90%
real skills for life.

00:15:10.900 --> 00:15:13.410 align:middle line:84%
But let's start with
the adults first.

00:15:13.410 --> 00:15:16.170 align:middle line:84%
First of all, if
you're participating

00:15:16.170 --> 00:15:19.820 align:middle line:84%
in these community
projects, and it's

00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:27.350 align:middle line:84%
from bakery to engineering
to chemicals to new materials

00:15:27.350 --> 00:15:30.660 align:middle line:84%
development to technology
to rocket science

00:15:30.660 --> 00:15:33.790 align:middle line:84%
to growing food to
purifying water,

00:15:33.790 --> 00:15:36.230 align:middle line:84%
you're going to be active in
all these community projects.

00:15:36.230 --> 00:15:39.220 align:middle line:84%
Sooner or later, you're going
to go and work in those areas.

00:15:39.220 --> 00:15:43.380 align:middle line:84%
Within a few years, the people
of our town and our community

00:15:43.380 --> 00:15:46.820 align:middle line:84%
will be so well trained
and so well informed

00:15:46.820 --> 00:15:50.500 align:middle line:84%
in all these areas, far
more hands-on knowledge

00:15:50.500 --> 00:15:52.532 align:middle line:84%
and hands-on
experience, we'll be

00:15:52.532 --> 00:15:53.990 align:middle line:84%
able to do everything
and anything,

00:15:53.990 --> 00:15:56.390 align:middle line:90%
because we've actually done it.

00:15:56.390 --> 00:15:59.140 align:middle line:84%
You've assisted or
worked in these areas.

00:15:59.140 --> 00:16:01.480 align:middle line:84%
You'll know how to bake
bread, how to make cheese,

00:16:01.480 --> 00:16:05.750 align:middle line:84%
how to build a rocket,
how to milk a cow.

00:16:05.750 --> 00:16:07.140 align:middle line:90%
I recently milked a cow.

00:16:07.140 --> 00:16:09.590 align:middle line:84%
It's first time that I
milked a cow in years.

00:16:09.590 --> 00:16:11.860 align:middle line:84%
It was such an
amazing experience.

00:16:11.860 --> 00:16:13.312 align:middle line:90%
It was like wow.

00:16:13.312 --> 00:16:15.520 align:middle line:84%
And I know that some people
have a problem with that,

00:16:15.520 --> 00:16:17.990 align:middle line:84%
but that's another
discussion altogether.

00:16:17.990 --> 00:16:21.350 align:middle line:90%


00:16:21.350 --> 00:16:24.170 align:middle line:84%
The animals, what happens to
vegetarianism and all that?

00:16:24.170 --> 00:16:26.450 align:middle line:84%
It's all part of the
growth of consciousness.

00:16:26.450 --> 00:16:28.700 align:middle line:84%
So let's put it out
there and say, yes, it

00:16:28.700 --> 00:16:30.870 align:middle line:90%
is something that is considered.

00:16:30.870 --> 00:16:33.700 align:middle line:84%
It is a very important
subject matter.

00:16:33.700 --> 00:16:37.630 align:middle line:84%
But it is part of the growth
of this unity consciousness

00:16:37.630 --> 00:16:40.370 align:middle line:84%
that we start to
growing into realizing

00:16:40.370 --> 00:16:42.760 align:middle line:84%
in our own personal
capacity, start

00:16:42.760 --> 00:16:44.057 align:middle line:90%
growing into that awareness.

00:16:44.057 --> 00:16:46.390 align:middle line:84%
And sooner or later, you'll
get to the point you'll say,

00:16:46.390 --> 00:16:48.720 align:middle line:84%
I can no longer drink
milk from a cow,

00:16:48.720 --> 00:16:51.710 align:middle line:90%
when the time is right for you.

00:16:51.710 --> 00:16:53.170 align:middle line:90%
We can't force that on anybody.

00:16:53.170 --> 00:16:55.570 align:middle line:84%
We can't force people
to be vegetarians.

00:16:55.570 --> 00:16:58.380 align:middle line:84%
It's part of our
individual growth

00:16:58.380 --> 00:17:01.140 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness that
becomes-- hopefully

00:17:01.140 --> 00:17:07.630 align:middle line:84%
will speed up as this
philosophy comes into fruition.

00:17:07.630 --> 00:17:12.990 align:middle line:84%
So what this really means is
that the sooner we implement

00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.940 align:middle line:84%
the community
projects, the sooner we

00:17:14.940 --> 00:17:18.640 align:middle line:84%
start creating a
really well integrated

00:17:18.640 --> 00:17:22.310 align:middle line:84%
and a united community of well
informed and highly skilled

00:17:22.310 --> 00:17:25.359 align:middle line:84%
people that know how to
do everything and have

00:17:25.359 --> 00:17:27.540 align:middle line:84%
no fear of anything
because they participate

00:17:27.540 --> 00:17:29.300 align:middle line:90%
in all this activity.

00:17:29.300 --> 00:17:34.120 align:middle line:84%
And the teachers, the masters
of the different areas

00:17:34.120 --> 00:17:37.310 align:middle line:84%
of the projects, whether it's
the baker or the engineer

00:17:37.310 --> 00:17:42.450 align:middle line:84%
or the rocket scientist or
the farmer or the anything,

00:17:42.450 --> 00:17:47.140 align:middle line:84%
clearly we're going to have
the best people in charge

00:17:47.140 --> 00:17:48.260 align:middle line:90%
of those areas.

00:17:48.260 --> 00:17:49.770 align:middle line:84%
We're not just going
to put somebody

00:17:49.770 --> 00:17:51.480 align:middle line:84%
who doesn't know
how to grow food

00:17:51.480 --> 00:17:53.890 align:middle line:84%
or how to build bridges
in charge of that area.

00:17:53.890 --> 00:17:55.890 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to have
the best people possible.

00:17:55.890 --> 00:17:59.620 align:middle line:84%
Those individuals ultimately
become the master teachers

00:17:59.620 --> 00:18:02.560 align:middle line:84%
in the community of
that specific subject.

00:18:02.560 --> 00:18:04.810 align:middle line:84%
Think about our current
education system.

00:18:04.810 --> 00:18:07.010 align:middle line:84%
And this is with all due
respect to the teachers

00:18:07.010 --> 00:18:09.434 align:middle line:84%
out there, because I know
that many of the teachers that

00:18:09.434 --> 00:18:10.850 align:middle line:84%
go out there
actually go out there

00:18:10.850 --> 00:18:13.624 align:middle line:84%
with a passion for teaching
and the love of teaching

00:18:13.624 --> 00:18:14.540 align:middle line:90%
and sharing knowledge.

00:18:14.540 --> 00:18:17.550 align:middle line:84%
But unfortunately they get
caught up in the system

00:18:17.550 --> 00:18:19.880 align:middle line:84%
and they are forced
to teach in a way

00:18:19.880 --> 00:18:22.340 align:middle line:84%
that they don't
necessarily want to teach.

00:18:22.340 --> 00:18:24.300 align:middle line:84%
But how could you
possibly call yourself

00:18:24.300 --> 00:18:27.910 align:middle line:84%
a teacher unless you are a
master of what is that you do?

00:18:27.910 --> 00:18:29.520 align:middle line:84%
If you don't know
how to bake, how

00:18:29.520 --> 00:18:31.520 align:middle line:84%
can you teach
someone else to bake

00:18:31.520 --> 00:18:33.650 align:middle line:90%
from a textbook in a classroom?

00:18:33.650 --> 00:18:35.440 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't work, does it?

00:18:35.440 --> 00:18:37.390 align:middle line:84%
If you don't know how
to build a bridge,

00:18:37.390 --> 00:18:40.420 align:middle line:84%
how could you tell somebody in
theory how to build a bridge?

00:18:40.420 --> 00:18:44.310 align:middle line:84%
So this is why I believe that
we don't need classrooms.

00:18:44.310 --> 00:18:47.930 align:middle line:84%
Hands-on experience
is far more important

00:18:47.930 --> 00:18:51.200 align:middle line:84%
that teaches us real skills for
life, not theoretical knowledge

00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:52.020 align:middle line:90%
or information.

00:18:52.020 --> 00:18:54.400 align:middle line:84%
There is no such
thing as failure.

00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:56.850 align:middle line:84%
This whole concept
of failing an exam

00:18:56.850 --> 00:19:00.660 align:middle line:84%
is just another example
how the fear tactics

00:19:00.660 --> 00:19:03.420 align:middle line:84%
and the fear-mongering
is imposed on our society

00:19:03.420 --> 00:19:05.720 align:middle line:84%
and on our children from
the earliest of ages.

00:19:05.720 --> 00:19:09.350 align:middle line:84%
The fear of failing an exam,
failing and not moving on

00:19:09.350 --> 00:19:11.670 align:middle line:90%
in life, how is that possible?

00:19:11.670 --> 00:19:13.570 align:middle line:84%
You're a living,
breathing human being.

00:19:13.570 --> 00:19:15.050 align:middle line:90%
You're already alive.

00:19:15.050 --> 00:19:16.660 align:middle line:90%
How can you fail?

00:19:16.660 --> 00:19:19.090 align:middle line:90%
We can't fail.

00:19:19.090 --> 00:19:22.220 align:middle line:84%
We choose to do
things we love to do.

00:19:22.220 --> 00:19:25.000 align:middle line:84%
And when you choose to do what
you love to do, how could you

00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:26.694 align:middle line:90%
possibly fail?

00:19:26.694 --> 00:19:28.360 align:middle line:84%
The only reason we
fail is because we're

00:19:28.360 --> 00:19:31.250 align:middle line:84%
forced to do things
we don't love to do.

00:19:31.250 --> 00:19:34.990 align:middle line:84%
And then they use
our lack of resonance

00:19:34.990 --> 00:19:38.330 align:middle line:84%
with what we're forced to do as
an expression that you failed,

00:19:38.330 --> 00:19:40.290 align:middle line:84%
because look how badly
you've done this.

00:19:40.290 --> 00:19:42.130 align:middle line:84%
So that all flies
out the window.

00:19:42.130 --> 00:19:44.510 align:middle line:84%
No longer do we see
ourselves as failures

00:19:44.510 --> 00:19:46.470 align:middle line:90%
in any sense whatsoever.

00:19:46.470 --> 00:19:49.060 align:middle line:84%
And that changes the
whole energetic structure

00:19:49.060 --> 00:19:51.900 align:middle line:84%
of our society and our
community very quickly.

00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:55.642 align:middle line:84%
So practical knowledge, we've
already spoken about the jobs,

00:19:55.642 --> 00:19:56.600 align:middle line:90%
that there are no jobs.

00:19:56.600 --> 00:19:58.610 align:middle line:90%
They're really labors of love.

00:19:58.610 --> 00:20:01.670 align:middle line:84%
And that leads us to
the fact that whatever

00:20:01.670 --> 00:20:03.340 align:middle line:84%
it is for your
community-- and somebody

00:20:03.340 --> 00:20:06.640 align:middle line:90%
brought this up earlier.

00:20:06.640 --> 00:20:08.330 align:middle line:84%
If you do something
for your community

00:20:08.330 --> 00:20:10.500 align:middle line:84%
that benefits the
community, that's

00:20:10.500 --> 00:20:13.760 align:middle line:84%
what you are known for
and respected and loved

00:20:13.760 --> 00:20:15.920 align:middle line:84%
and cherished, because
everybody knows

00:20:15.920 --> 00:20:19.540 align:middle line:84%
that Michael is the guy
that bakes the best bread.

00:20:19.540 --> 00:20:23.260 align:middle line:84%
And they love you for it,
because they love your bread,

00:20:23.260 --> 00:20:26.210 align:middle line:84%
or they love the way
that you make shoes

00:20:26.210 --> 00:20:28.490 align:middle line:90%
or whatever it is that you do.

00:20:28.490 --> 00:20:32.250 align:middle line:84%
You're respected because
of what you contribute

00:20:32.250 --> 00:20:35.280 align:middle line:84%
to your community, not because
how much money you have

00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:39.390 align:middle line:84%
or how many people you
employ and give them

00:20:39.390 --> 00:20:42.680 align:middle line:84%
the illusion of
security, you know,

00:20:42.680 --> 00:20:45.420 align:middle line:84%
because that's why I said
today the respect we carry

00:20:45.420 --> 00:20:48.720 align:middle line:84%
in our society today is
actually a completely

00:20:48.720 --> 00:20:51.830 align:middle line:90%
misguided sense of respect.

00:20:51.830 --> 00:20:54.000 align:middle line:84%
It's more of a fear-based
kind of gratitude.

00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:56.590 align:middle line:84%
Thank god this guy's
giving us a job.

00:20:56.590 --> 00:20:58.260 align:middle line:90%
We really respect you for that.

00:20:58.260 --> 00:20:59.060 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:20:59.060 --> 00:21:00.120 align:middle line:90%
That's not respect.

00:21:00.120 --> 00:21:02.870 align:middle line:84%
That's a fear-based
kind of servitude.

00:21:02.870 --> 00:21:07.510 align:middle line:84%
So this really causes a rapid
rise in unity consciousness

00:21:07.510 --> 00:21:10.540 align:middle line:84%
as people pursue their
passions, because out

00:21:10.540 --> 00:21:14.400 align:middle line:84%
of 168 hours in
a week, you still

00:21:14.400 --> 00:21:18.590 align:middle line:84%
have 165 hours to
do what you love.

00:21:18.590 --> 00:21:22.260 align:middle line:84%
What are you going to do
with all that time, right?

00:21:22.260 --> 00:21:25.640 align:middle line:84%
And this is where it
really starts to-- wow.

00:21:25.640 --> 00:21:30.670 align:middle line:84%
Today we work like slaves
just to stay alive.

00:21:30.670 --> 00:21:33.130 align:middle line:84%
With this kind of system,
three hours a week

00:21:33.130 --> 00:21:36.440 align:middle line:84%
in the community
project, what I find

00:21:36.440 --> 00:21:41.112 align:middle line:84%
and what many people seem to
believe is that most of us

00:21:41.112 --> 00:21:43.320 align:middle line:84%
will probably work a lot
more than three hours a week

00:21:43.320 --> 00:21:44.510 align:middle line:90%
in the community projects.

00:21:44.510 --> 00:21:45.680 align:middle line:90%
>>I was just thinking that.

00:21:45.680 --> 00:21:47.510 align:middle line:84%
>>Because you're going to
find something you love.

00:21:47.510 --> 00:21:49.550 align:middle line:84%
Like you might-- because
of the different things

00:21:49.550 --> 00:21:51.430 align:middle line:84%
that you're now
exposed to, you're

00:21:51.430 --> 00:21:54.410 align:middle line:84%
going to suddenly find that you
love the chemical engineering

00:21:54.410 --> 00:21:54.700 align:middle line:90%
part.

00:21:54.700 --> 00:21:55.730 align:middle line:84%
And you'll say,
well, listen, I want

00:21:55.730 --> 00:21:57.680 align:middle line:84%
to spend more time
in the chemistry lab,

00:21:57.680 --> 00:22:00.000 align:middle line:84%
because I love this stuff
and I'll get some ideas

00:22:00.000 --> 00:22:01.379 align:middle line:90%
about developing new materials.

00:22:01.379 --> 00:22:03.420 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to say,
yeah, sure, great, what

00:22:03.420 --> 00:22:05.510 align:middle line:84%
are your ideas, because
that's how it works.

00:22:05.510 --> 00:22:05.730 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:22:05.730 --> 00:22:06.200 align:middle line:90%
Sorry.

00:22:06.200 --> 00:22:06.830 align:middle line:90%
You're an idiot.

00:22:06.830 --> 00:22:07.400 align:middle line:90%
Go away.

00:22:07.400 --> 00:22:08.370 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:22:08.370 --> 00:22:10.078 align:middle line:84%
They'll invite you in
and say, all right.

00:22:10.078 --> 00:22:11.230 align:middle line:90%
What are you thinking?

00:22:11.230 --> 00:22:12.350 align:middle line:90%
What should we try?

00:22:12.350 --> 00:22:15.670 align:middle line:84%
And experiment, because
that's what this is all about,

00:22:15.670 --> 00:22:17.830 align:middle line:84%
learning through
experimentation,

00:22:17.830 --> 00:22:22.050 align:middle line:84%
playing, because that's the
opportunity that you have.

00:22:22.050 --> 00:22:25.660 align:middle line:84%
And it's all there for you
presented by the community.

00:22:25.660 --> 00:22:29.960 align:middle line:84%
So it really explodes
with possibility.

00:22:29.960 --> 00:22:32.970 align:middle line:84%
You decided that you
love breeding fish

00:22:32.970 --> 00:22:36.070 align:middle line:84%
and you just have
a knack for this.

00:22:36.070 --> 00:22:39.590 align:middle line:84%
And to breed the fish
better and quicker,

00:22:39.590 --> 00:22:41.481 align:middle line:84%
we're going to need
highly oxygenated water.

00:22:41.481 --> 00:22:43.980 align:middle line:84%
So then we're going to need the
scientists and the guys that

00:22:43.980 --> 00:22:47.220 align:middle line:84%
know how to energize and
oxygenate water naturally

00:22:47.220 --> 00:22:48.880 align:middle line:84%
from the streams
and the rivers that

00:22:48.880 --> 00:22:51.210 align:middle line:90%
feed through our fish farm.

00:22:51.210 --> 00:22:54.260 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, our fish
grow three times as quickly

00:22:54.260 --> 00:22:58.640 align:middle line:84%
and they taste
better and they look

00:22:58.640 --> 00:23:01.920 align:middle line:84%
better for those that want to
breed koi fish not necessarily

00:23:01.920 --> 00:23:04.430 align:middle line:90%
fish to eat.

00:23:04.430 --> 00:23:06.360 align:middle line:90%
Everything becomes possible.

00:23:06.360 --> 00:23:11.080 align:middle line:84%
So everything becomes
a community project.

00:23:11.080 --> 00:23:13.955 align:middle line:84%
And here's an
interesting example.

00:23:13.955 --> 00:23:15.790 align:middle line:90%
I'm a painter.

00:23:15.790 --> 00:23:18.930 align:middle line:90%
I paint beautiful paintings.

00:23:18.930 --> 00:23:21.350 align:middle line:84%
And I get my canvases
from the guys

00:23:21.350 --> 00:23:24.736 align:middle line:84%
that create canvases
in town for free.

00:23:24.736 --> 00:23:26.530 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that amazing?

00:23:26.530 --> 00:23:29.320 align:middle line:84%
And normally they'd cost
you a bloody fortune,

00:23:29.320 --> 00:23:30.565 align:middle line:90%
to buy a canvas these days.

00:23:30.565 --> 00:23:33.140 align:middle line:84%
And the paintbrushes are
real wooden paintbrushes

00:23:33.140 --> 00:23:34.520 align:middle line:90%
with real horsehair.

00:23:34.520 --> 00:23:37.430 align:middle line:84%
And today, that's
very, very expensive.

00:23:37.430 --> 00:23:39.590 align:middle line:84%
And my paintbrushes
are prepared for me

00:23:39.590 --> 00:23:42.130 align:middle line:84%
by the guys that make
paintbrushes in my town.

00:23:42.130 --> 00:23:45.090 align:middle line:84%
And I use this,
this is my hobby.

00:23:45.090 --> 00:23:47.950 align:middle line:84%
This is my labor of love,
what I do for myself.

00:23:47.950 --> 00:23:52.310 align:middle line:84%
So I start to paint, and I
make these beautiful paintings.

00:23:52.310 --> 00:23:54.409 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly people start
coming to me saying,

00:23:54.409 --> 00:23:56.200 align:middle line:84%
Michael, wow, we really
love your painting.

00:23:56.200 --> 00:23:59.560 align:middle line:84%
Can you paint me a picture
of that mountain over there?

00:23:59.560 --> 00:24:00.370 align:middle line:90%
I say sure.

00:24:00.370 --> 00:24:01.786 align:middle line:84%
And I'll paint a
beautiful picture

00:24:01.786 --> 00:24:03.060 align:middle line:90%
of the mountain for John.

00:24:03.060 --> 00:24:04.830 align:middle line:84%
And John takes it and
everyone goes, wow,

00:24:04.830 --> 00:24:05.610 align:middle line:90%
John, that's amazing.

00:24:05.610 --> 00:24:06.070 align:middle line:90%
Who did that?

00:24:06.070 --> 00:24:06.890 align:middle line:90%
Michael did that.

00:24:06.890 --> 00:24:07.530 align:middle line:90%
Oh, wow.

00:24:07.530 --> 00:24:08.660 align:middle line:90%
Michael, can you do that--

00:24:08.660 --> 00:24:10.184 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly before
you know, people

00:24:10.184 --> 00:24:11.850 align:middle line:84%
are coming to you
from your town saying,

00:24:11.850 --> 00:24:13.641 align:middle line:84%
can you do this painting
and that painting?

00:24:13.641 --> 00:24:16.200 align:middle line:84%
And then suddenly
people say, Michael,

00:24:16.200 --> 00:24:18.620 align:middle line:90%
you're the best painter in town.

00:24:18.620 --> 00:24:20.510 align:middle line:84%
Can you teach our
children how to paint?

00:24:20.510 --> 00:24:22.760 align:middle line:84%
And automatically, people
gravitate towards you

00:24:22.760 --> 00:24:24.510 align:middle line:90%
to teach them how to paint.

00:24:24.510 --> 00:24:28.130 align:middle line:84%
So at some stage, the council
of elders will call you in

00:24:28.130 --> 00:24:31.780 align:middle line:84%
and say, Michael, everybody
loves you as a painter.

00:24:31.780 --> 00:24:34.090 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to take on
the role as the master

00:24:34.090 --> 00:24:36.120 align:middle line:90%
painter of our community?

00:24:36.120 --> 00:24:38.890 align:middle line:84%
And then you have a choice
to say either yes or no,

00:24:38.890 --> 00:24:41.000 align:middle line:90%
because it's your choice.

00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:42.494 align:middle line:90%
You're not forced into it.

00:24:42.494 --> 00:24:44.160 align:middle line:84%
And if you take on
that choice, then you

00:24:44.160 --> 00:24:45.430 align:middle line:90%
become the master painter.

00:24:45.430 --> 00:24:46.310 align:middle line:90%
But you know what?

00:24:46.310 --> 00:24:48.230 align:middle line:84%
You've already become
the master painter.

00:24:48.230 --> 00:24:50.700 align:middle line:84%
Whether you accept it or not,
the people have chosen you.

00:24:50.700 --> 00:24:52.970 align:middle line:84%
It's just that the
council of elders

00:24:52.970 --> 00:24:56.360 align:middle line:84%
will give you I guess the
platform to say, look,

00:24:56.360 --> 00:24:58.520 align:middle line:84%
we acknowledge you
as the master painter

00:24:58.520 --> 00:25:00.620 align:middle line:90%
more than anything else.

00:25:00.620 --> 00:25:03.960 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, before you
know, you say, well, look,

00:25:03.960 --> 00:25:06.760 align:middle line:84%
you no longer have to do three
hours a week in the community

00:25:06.760 --> 00:25:09.310 align:middle line:84%
project, because everybody
needs to come to you

00:25:09.310 --> 00:25:14.410 align:middle line:84%
as your paint workshop is now
the new community project,

00:25:14.410 --> 00:25:17.740 align:middle line:84%
because everybody's coming
to you to learn how to paint.

00:25:17.740 --> 00:25:19.750 align:middle line:84%
And now you need
the actual paint,

00:25:19.750 --> 00:25:22.340 align:middle line:84%
so that comes from the
chemists in the lab that

00:25:22.340 --> 00:25:24.140 align:middle line:90%
are creating the paint for you.

00:25:24.140 --> 00:25:27.070 align:middle line:84%
But the paint is
biodegradable, nontoxic,

00:25:27.070 --> 00:25:29.170 align:middle line:84%
and you get multiple
colors, far more

00:25:29.170 --> 00:25:31.690 align:middle line:84%
than you get from the
current laboratories that

00:25:31.690 --> 00:25:34.130 align:middle line:90%
make the poisonous paint.

00:25:34.130 --> 00:25:38.160 align:middle line:84%
And everything that you get is
made out of the best materials

00:25:38.160 --> 00:25:42.770 align:middle line:84%
and it's nontoxic and
biodegradable and free,

00:25:42.770 --> 00:25:45.480 align:middle line:84%
because you get it because
you're part of the community.

00:25:45.480 --> 00:25:47.700 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't get
the paint, then you

00:25:47.700 --> 00:25:50.280 align:middle line:84%
go to the chemists
in the chemical lab,

00:25:50.280 --> 00:25:52.320 align:middle line:84%
and say, listen, I need
the following colors

00:25:52.320 --> 00:25:53.900 align:middle line:90%
for my paint shop.

00:25:53.900 --> 00:25:57.700 align:middle line:84%
And they create it for you,
because that's what they do.

00:25:57.700 --> 00:26:01.940 align:middle line:84%
Can you see how simple
and integrated this?

00:26:01.940 --> 00:26:05.040 align:middle line:84%
It's insane that
anything else is actually

00:26:05.040 --> 00:26:09.190 align:middle line:84%
been allowed to rise and
consume our lives, anything

00:26:09.190 --> 00:26:13.780 align:middle line:84%
other than this kind of way
of thinking and philosophy.

00:26:13.780 --> 00:26:17.310 align:middle line:84%
So when I say everything
becomes a community project,

00:26:17.310 --> 00:26:19.070 align:middle line:84%
I hope that it's now
making more sense

00:26:19.070 --> 00:26:22.430 align:middle line:84%
and that it's easy to comprehend
that kind of statement

00:26:22.430 --> 00:26:25.977 align:middle line:84%
and how that expands
the community projects.

00:26:25.977 --> 00:26:27.560 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly we're going
to need to create

00:26:27.560 --> 00:26:30.000 align:middle line:84%
more paint, for not
just painting houses,

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:32.226 align:middle line:90%
but for artists.

00:26:32.226 --> 00:26:34.600 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to need to
create different kind of clays

00:26:34.600 --> 00:26:37.500 align:middle line:84%
for the sculptors and materials
with which they sculpt.

00:26:37.500 --> 00:26:38.760 align:middle line:90%
And it might not just be clay.

00:26:38.760 --> 00:26:43.890 align:middle line:84%
It might be a graphene kind
of material mixed with hemp

00:26:43.890 --> 00:26:47.530 align:middle line:84%
or whatever that is
moldable and biodegradable

00:26:47.530 --> 00:26:50.550 align:middle line:84%
and is far stronger
and doesn't break.

00:26:50.550 --> 00:26:54.870 align:middle line:84%
So our needs for materials
will change totally.

00:26:54.870 --> 00:26:57.130 align:middle line:84%
So this brings us to
another consideration,

00:26:57.130 --> 00:26:59.950 align:middle line:84%
and that is, how do
we invite and include

00:26:59.950 --> 00:27:03.720 align:middle line:84%
existing businesses and
companies and factories

00:27:03.720 --> 00:27:07.280 align:middle line:84%
and industry to participate
in this creation of abundance?

00:27:07.280 --> 00:27:09.090 align:middle line:84%
And this is really
a beautiful example

00:27:09.090 --> 00:27:12.750 align:middle line:84%
that demonstrates how
inclusive this philosophy

00:27:12.750 --> 00:27:14.710 align:middle line:90%
of Contributionism is.

00:27:14.710 --> 00:27:16.140 align:middle line:90%
It does not exclude anyone.

00:27:16.140 --> 00:27:18.640 align:middle line:84%
It always invites
everyone to participate

00:27:18.640 --> 00:27:20.870 align:middle line:90%
in this abundance creation.

00:27:20.870 --> 00:27:23.610 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to use an
example of a little factory

00:27:23.610 --> 00:27:24.830 align:middle line:90%
that we have in our town.

00:27:24.830 --> 00:27:29.670 align:middle line:84%
They make door windows and--
wooden doors and windows.

00:27:29.670 --> 00:27:32.290 align:middle line:84%
So what we do is
we invite everybody

00:27:32.290 --> 00:27:35.920 align:middle line:84%
to participate in becoming
a community project.

00:27:35.920 --> 00:27:38.150 align:middle line:84%
And normally, the
question is-- first

00:27:38.150 --> 00:27:41.400 align:middle line:84%
an immediate question is, well,
what's in it for me, right?

00:27:41.400 --> 00:27:42.910 align:middle line:90%
So the answer is very simple.

00:27:42.910 --> 00:27:44.960 align:middle line:84%
You already know what
the answer is, right?

00:27:44.960 --> 00:27:48.140 align:middle line:84%
What's in it for you
as a factory owner is

00:27:48.140 --> 00:27:54.250 align:middle line:84%
free electricity; no rent; no
rates and taxes; free labor,

00:27:54.250 --> 00:27:56.760 align:middle line:84%
because now that you're part
of the community project,

00:27:56.760 --> 00:27:58.520 align:middle line:84%
people will be allocated
to come and work

00:27:58.520 --> 00:28:01.300 align:middle line:84%
in your factory; free
wood, because you'll

00:28:01.300 --> 00:28:03.950 align:middle line:84%
get the wood from our sawmill,
because the sawmill is

00:28:03.950 --> 00:28:07.660 align:middle line:84%
a community project;
free glue, because you'll

00:28:07.660 --> 00:28:10.570 align:middle line:84%
get the glue from our
chemical laboratory that's

00:28:10.570 --> 00:28:14.550 align:middle line:84%
going to be better and stronger,
nontoxic and biodegradable glue

00:28:14.550 --> 00:28:17.250 align:middle line:90%
that you can't afford today.

00:28:17.250 --> 00:28:20.760 align:middle line:84%
And any other components that
you need for your factory

00:28:20.760 --> 00:28:22.200 align:middle line:90%
will be provided for you.

00:28:22.200 --> 00:28:25.000 align:middle line:90%
So that's what's in it for you.

00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:28.070 align:middle line:84%
And all you have to do
in return is manage that,

00:28:28.070 --> 00:28:33.540 align:middle line:84%
be the master carpenter, and
teach the people what to do.

00:28:33.540 --> 00:28:38.010 align:middle line:84%
And in return, you retain
1/3 of the profits and 2/3

00:28:38.010 --> 00:28:39.650 align:middle line:90%
go back to the community.

00:28:39.650 --> 00:28:41.650 align:middle line:84%
And guess what people say
when you approach them

00:28:41.650 --> 00:28:44.540 align:middle line:84%
with this, whether they're
farmers, whether they're

00:28:44.540 --> 00:28:47.720 align:middle line:84%
factory owners, doesn't
matter what field of work

00:28:47.720 --> 00:28:50.730 align:middle line:84%
they come from, the
answer is always the same.

00:28:50.730 --> 00:28:52.750 align:middle line:90%
When can we start?

00:28:52.750 --> 00:28:55.140 align:middle line:84%
You don't even
enter a negotiation,

00:28:55.140 --> 00:28:57.410 align:middle line:84%
because suddenly
they've got no cost

00:28:57.410 --> 00:28:59.330 align:middle line:84%
and you're offering
them all the stuff,

00:28:59.330 --> 00:29:01.920 align:middle line:84%
the expertise that they
can't afford today.

00:29:01.920 --> 00:29:04.260 align:middle line:84%
And they retain
1/3 of the profits?

00:29:04.260 --> 00:29:06.050 align:middle line:90%
It's a no-brainer, right?

00:29:06.050 --> 00:29:09.620 align:middle line:84%
So this is how beautiful
and elegant this system is,

00:29:09.620 --> 00:29:12.300 align:middle line:84%
and how you invite everybody
into your community.

00:29:12.300 --> 00:29:17.000 align:middle line:84%
And this is why whether
it's computer geeks building

00:29:17.000 --> 00:29:22.380 align:middle line:84%
supercomputers or any kind
of manufacturing, research,

00:29:22.380 --> 00:29:25.755 align:middle line:84%
or industry that's
doing things, people

00:29:25.755 --> 00:29:27.660 align:middle line:84%
will start to come
to your community

00:29:27.660 --> 00:29:30.440 align:middle line:84%
and say, can I make my
business and my factory

00:29:30.440 --> 00:29:33.470 align:middle line:84%
part of your community projects,
because suddenly they'll

00:29:33.470 --> 00:29:36.080 align:middle line:84%
realize that it's a
huge benefit to them.

00:29:36.080 --> 00:29:39.270 align:middle line:84%
