00:49:54.480 --> 00:49:58.570 align:middle line:84%
with people doing these kind
of meetings and meetup groups,

00:49:58.570 --> 00:50:04.830 align:middle line:84%
so the intention is that we
have an easy-to-watch shorter

00:50:04.830 --> 00:50:08.610 align:middle line:84%
version of kind of a workshop,
either on DVD or a flash drive

00:50:08.610 --> 00:50:12.010 align:middle line:84%
or downloadable from the
website that anybody anywhere

00:50:12.010 --> 00:50:14.990 align:middle line:84%
can get so it's
the same workshop

00:50:14.990 --> 00:50:16.750 align:middle line:84%
so people don't fill
in their own ideas.

00:50:16.750 --> 00:50:19.034 align:middle line:84%
What I've found is
that often people

00:50:19.034 --> 00:50:21.450 align:middle line:84%
get a sniff of this idea, they
read a little bit about it,

00:50:21.450 --> 00:50:23.432 align:middle line:84%
and they get the wrong
end of the stick.

00:50:23.432 --> 00:50:25.390 align:middle line:84%
And they run out there
and they try and promote

00:50:25.390 --> 00:50:27.223 align:middle line:84%
this Ubuntu philosophy,
but they're actually

00:50:27.223 --> 00:50:29.580 align:middle line:84%
promoting a very
different kind of idea

00:50:29.580 --> 00:50:32.030 align:middle line:84%
and then they get it all
wrong and they confuse people.

00:50:32.030 --> 00:50:34.200 align:middle line:84%
So what we've got to be
very careful about here

00:50:34.200 --> 00:50:36.640 align:middle line:84%
is that we stick to the
knitting and we keep

00:50:36.640 --> 00:50:38.640 align:middle line:90%
promoting the same philosophy.

00:50:38.640 --> 00:50:41.950 align:middle line:84%
So I think what I need to do is
create like a DVD or something

00:50:41.950 --> 00:50:44.240 align:middle line:84%
that we can make available
or download so it's

00:50:44.240 --> 00:50:46.150 align:middle line:84%
the same presentation
that everybody

00:50:46.150 --> 00:50:49.350 align:middle line:84%
gets the same steps
and the guidelines.

00:50:49.350 --> 00:50:51.560 align:middle line:84%
So everybody can then
take that and say, OK,

00:50:51.560 --> 00:50:52.874 align:middle line:90%
come to my house for a meeting.

00:50:52.874 --> 00:50:55.040 align:middle line:84%
We have a little group
gathering, talk about a world

00:50:55.040 --> 00:50:55.840 align:middle line:90%
without money.

00:50:55.840 --> 00:50:57.790 align:middle line:84%
You put this onto
your computer or TV.

00:50:57.790 --> 00:51:00.760 align:middle line:84%
You show everybody the DVD, so
everybody shows the same thing

00:51:00.760 --> 00:51:02.920 align:middle line:84%
and they don't put their
own ideology into it,

00:51:02.920 --> 00:51:05.390 align:middle line:84%
because that's what I
found was a mistake that I

00:51:05.390 --> 00:51:06.900 align:middle line:90%
made some time ago.

00:51:06.900 --> 00:51:09.590 align:middle line:84%
And it backfired
on us quite badly,

00:51:09.590 --> 00:51:11.600 align:middle line:84%
where I just assumed
people would get it.

00:51:11.600 --> 00:51:12.400 align:middle line:90%
But no.

00:51:12.400 --> 00:51:14.500 align:middle line:84%
It takes a little bit
of training and guidance

00:51:14.500 --> 00:51:17.430 align:middle line:84%
to really get to the core
understanding of this.

00:51:17.430 --> 00:51:20.480 align:middle line:84%
And we've been through two
days here in the studio,

00:51:20.480 --> 00:51:23.050 align:middle line:84%
and I think finally
now you have it

00:51:23.050 --> 00:51:25.760 align:middle line:84%
and it's a lot easier for you to
go and share this with others.

00:51:25.760 --> 00:51:27.910 align:middle line:84%
But if you just spend an
hour or two with people,

00:51:27.910 --> 00:51:30.130 align:middle line:90%
often that's not enough.

00:51:30.130 --> 00:51:36.910 align:middle line:84%
So it's going to have to be
that focused workshop that's

00:51:36.910 --> 00:51:41.610 align:middle line:84%
available to everyone, that is
the same ethos and philosophy,

00:51:41.610 --> 00:51:43.850 align:middle line:90%
without diluting it.

00:51:43.850 --> 00:51:46.720 align:middle line:84%
But also what I
must say is that we

00:51:46.720 --> 00:51:49.140 align:middle line:84%
have a database on
the Ubuntu website

00:51:49.140 --> 00:51:51.240 align:middle line:90%
from people all over the world.

00:51:51.240 --> 00:51:53.840 align:middle line:84%
And the plan of
action is actually--

00:51:53.840 --> 00:51:56.780 align:middle line:84%
and again, because we have
so little support in admin

00:51:56.780 --> 00:52:00.780 align:middle line:90%
and IT support, it's been tough.

00:52:00.780 --> 00:52:02.610 align:middle line:90%
It's been tough going.

00:52:02.610 --> 00:52:04.875 align:middle line:84%
Some people think that we've
got this big organization

00:52:04.875 --> 00:52:05.750 align:middle line:90%
doing all this stuff.

00:52:05.750 --> 00:52:06.550 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:52:06.550 --> 00:52:07.469 align:middle line:90%
It's me.

00:52:07.469 --> 00:52:08.510 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing all this stuff.

00:52:08.510 --> 00:52:09.843 align:middle line:90%
I have to answer all the emails.

00:52:09.843 --> 00:52:11.404 align:middle line:84%
I have to deal with
all the people,

00:52:11.404 --> 00:52:13.070 align:middle line:84%
either they're happy
or unhappy with me.

00:52:13.070 --> 00:52:15.840 align:middle line:84%
And Louisa's been
supporting in many ways,

00:52:15.840 --> 00:52:21.090 align:middle line:84%
but she's sort of going on a
whole different energetic part

00:52:21.090 --> 00:52:25.680 align:middle line:84%
of this, not the hands-on
political community project

00:52:25.680 --> 00:52:26.480 align:middle line:90%
philosophy.

00:52:26.480 --> 00:52:30.100 align:middle line:84%
She's moving away into the
whole energetic shamanic working

00:52:30.100 --> 00:52:33.500 align:middle line:84%
of this philosophy, which is a
very important aspect of this.

00:52:33.500 --> 00:52:36.510 align:middle line:84%
We're holding the space
as best as we can.

00:52:36.510 --> 00:52:39.790 align:middle line:84%
But what I do have is
I've got a database

00:52:39.790 --> 00:52:41.420 align:middle line:90%
of people in every country.

00:52:41.420 --> 00:52:43.290 align:middle line:84%
In the USA we've
got a huge database

00:52:43.290 --> 00:52:44.950 align:middle line:90%
of people that have signed up.

00:52:44.950 --> 00:52:47.650 align:middle line:84%
So the idea is to connect
all those people together

00:52:47.650 --> 00:52:50.890 align:middle line:84%
and those in communities
in close proximity

00:52:50.890 --> 00:52:54.610 align:middle line:84%
start meeting up physically, not
just virtually on the internet.

00:52:54.610 --> 00:52:55.650 align:middle line:90%
That's not good enough.

00:52:55.650 --> 00:52:58.670 align:middle line:84%
You've got to actually share
physical energy with each other

00:52:58.670 --> 00:53:01.690 align:middle line:84%
and get to know each other
and share this knowledge

00:53:01.690 --> 00:53:04.380 align:middle line:84%
face to face where you can
actually hug the person

00:53:04.380 --> 00:53:06.390 align:middle line:84%
and know that it's a
real living, breathing

00:53:06.390 --> 00:53:09.070 align:middle line:84%
human being and
not a cyberbuddy.

00:53:09.070 --> 00:53:13.780 align:middle line:84%
That's been part of the
problem is that we can't just

00:53:13.780 --> 00:53:17.460 align:middle line:84%
depend on the internet
and Facebook and emails

00:53:17.460 --> 00:53:19.300 align:middle line:84%
to connect people
around the world.

00:53:19.300 --> 00:53:21.270 align:middle line:90%
It has to be physical contact.

00:53:21.270 --> 00:53:23.580 align:middle line:84%
I've just had that
experience in Austria.

00:53:23.580 --> 00:53:26.390 align:middle line:84%
I was in a
mind-blowing experience

00:53:26.390 --> 00:53:29.570 align:middle line:84%
where I came from
Turkey to Austria

00:53:29.570 --> 00:53:32.630 align:middle line:84%
and Gernot Gauper, who's setting
up the Ubuntu party in Austria

00:53:32.630 --> 00:53:34.896 align:middle line:84%
now, just set up three
meetings in Vienna,

00:53:34.896 --> 00:53:36.270 align:middle line:84%
in Graz, and in
Salzburg, where I

00:53:36.270 --> 00:53:40.850 align:middle line:84%
walked into rooms filled with
more than 100 people that just

00:53:40.850 --> 00:53:43.310 align:middle line:84%
want to embrace this
philosophy and start the Ubuntu

00:53:43.310 --> 00:53:44.440 align:middle line:90%
movement in Austria.

00:53:44.440 --> 00:53:45.880 align:middle line:90%
It blew my mind.

00:53:45.880 --> 00:53:48.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's the energetic
exchange that you need,

00:53:48.410 --> 00:53:50.900 align:middle line:84%
where people gather
with the same intent,

00:53:50.900 --> 00:53:54.270 align:middle line:84%
the same-- the intention
is already there.

00:53:54.270 --> 00:53:57.870 align:middle line:84%
So this is what I'd like to
help share and facilitate

00:53:57.870 --> 00:54:01.840 align:middle line:84%
by putting the people in
contact in their communities

00:54:01.840 --> 00:54:06.000 align:middle line:84%
so you can really then exchange
details and start meeting up.

00:54:06.000 --> 00:54:09.070 align:middle line:84%
And I will do the best I can
to come and meet these groups

00:54:09.070 --> 00:54:12.330 align:middle line:84%
and have more of these kind
of face-to-face meetings

00:54:12.330 --> 00:54:15.800 align:middle line:84%
to maybe keep things
focused, because I've

00:54:15.800 --> 00:54:20.400 align:middle line:84%
seen how quickly things can
go off track very easily.

00:54:20.400 --> 00:54:22.790 align:middle line:90%
Let's wind up this episode.

00:54:22.790 --> 00:54:25.340 align:middle line:84%
It's the second-last
episode, and I look forward

00:54:25.340 --> 00:54:29.700 align:middle line:84%
to the final episode, where
we really unravel and answer

00:54:29.700 --> 00:54:31.100 align:middle line:90%
all the questions.

00:54:31.100 --> 00:54:32.920 align:middle line:84%
And this is the
really exciting part,

00:54:32.920 --> 00:54:34.900 align:middle line:84%
where I'd like each
and every one of you

00:54:34.900 --> 00:54:37.930 align:middle line:84%
to think about the
questions, the most difficult

00:54:37.930 --> 00:54:41.780 align:middle line:84%
and what you think is the most
insurmountable problem that we

00:54:41.780 --> 00:54:44.800 align:middle line:84%
may have in this world without
money and the communities.

00:54:44.800 --> 00:54:48.910 align:middle line:84%
And before we leave here and
finish these eight episodes,

00:54:48.910 --> 00:54:52.110 align:middle line:84%
I want us all to be
able to those questions

00:54:52.110 --> 00:54:55.350 align:middle line:84%
and know that we've
totally internalized this,

00:54:55.350 --> 00:54:57.020 align:middle line:84%
because until you've
internalized this

00:54:57.020 --> 00:54:59.420 align:middle line:84%
and you feel totally
comfortable with facing

00:54:59.420 --> 00:55:02.200 align:middle line:84%
any kind of question
from anyone in the world,

00:55:02.200 --> 00:55:04.220 align:middle line:90%
you have not yet embraced this.

00:55:04.220 --> 00:55:07.060 align:middle line:84%
You must not have any
fear from anyone thinking

00:55:07.060 --> 00:55:11.330 align:middle line:84%
that, oh, I hope he doesn't
ask me a difficult question.

00:55:11.330 --> 00:55:13.500 align:middle line:84%
Then you haven't
embraced it yet.

00:55:13.500 --> 00:55:16.720 align:middle line:84%
And this is where I'd like us
to leave with by the time we

00:55:16.720 --> 00:55:20.210 align:middle line:84%
finish these eight episodes,
knowing, being absolutely

00:55:20.210 --> 00:55:22.730 align:middle line:84%
confident no matter what
anyone throws at you,

00:55:22.730 --> 00:55:26.850 align:middle line:84%
that you feel in a position
of self-empowerment,

00:55:26.850 --> 00:55:29.880 align:middle line:84%
self-knowledge,
and self-resonating

00:55:29.880 --> 00:55:33.600 align:middle line:84%
with the simple philosophy that
you feel capable of handling

00:55:33.600 --> 00:55:34.770 align:middle line:90%
any kind of question.

00:55:34.770 --> 00:55:36.810 align:middle line:84%
So thanks for being
in the studio.

00:55:36.810 --> 00:55:40.380 align:middle line:84%
Thanks for being here
for this whole exercise.

00:55:40.380 --> 00:55:42.160 align:middle line:84%
We'll pick this up
in the final episode.

00:55:42.160 --> 00:55:42.960 align:middle line:90%
Thanks.

00:55:42.960 --> 00:55:45.485 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:55:45.485 --> 00:55:48.810 align:middle line:90%


00:55:48.810 --> 00:55:49.810 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for watching.

00:55:49.810 --> 00:55:51.870 align:middle line:90%
I'm Michael Tellinger.

